---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../styles/home-modern.css";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How We Work | Berrystock Solutions"
  description="Outcome-led architecture, secure by design, structured delivery. how Berrystock approaches every engagement."
>
  <div class="page-wrap">

    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="kicker">How we work</div>
        <h1 class="h-display">
          Architecture with a<br />
          <span class="accent">delivery plan behind it.</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="h-lead">
          Secure cloud platforms and integrated business systems. designed for
          clarity, built for operability, and structured so your team can own
          what we hand over.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- APPROACH -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h2">Our approach</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-num">01</div>
            <h3>Outcome-led architecture</h3>
            <p>We begin with business objectives, not tooling. Architecture decisions align to risk tolerance, growth plans, and operational maturity.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Clear platform structure</li>
              <li>Defined ownership and access models</li>
              <li>Scalable foundations</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-num">02</div>
            <h3>Secure by design</h3>
            <p>Identity-first access patterns and restricted management surfaces reduce risk without increasing operational friction.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>MFA and conditional access alignment</li>
              <li>Least-privilege access control</li>
              <li>Hardened management endpoints</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-num">03</div>
            <h3>Structured delivery</h3>
            <p>Change is delivered with staged rollout, rollback planning, and documented operating procedures. every time.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Cutover and rollback strategy</li>
              <li>Pre-flight validation</li>
              <li>Runbooks and handover docs</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-num">04</div>
            <h3>Business systems integration</h3>
            <p>We connect cloud infrastructure with ERP, CRM, telephony, and workflow automation to remove manual effort and improve visibility.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>System-to-system integration</li>
              <li>Email and identity alignment</li>
              <li>Structured data flows</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-num">05</div>
            <h3>Operational discipline</h3>
            <p>Platforms are designed to be maintainable. Visibility, monitoring, cost control, and change governance are embedded from day one.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Monitoring and alerting structure</li>
              <li>Cost optimisation controls</li>
              <li>Clear change management approach</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-num">06</div>
            <h3>Automation-driven engineering</h3>
            <p>Repeatable patterns reduce risk and accelerate delivery while ensuring environments remain consistent over time.</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Infrastructure as Code</li>
              <li>Deployment standardisation</li>
              <li>Operational scripting</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="cta-band">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="statement" style="margin: 0 auto 12px; text-align:center;">
          Ready to <span class="accent">move from plan to production?</span>
        </p>
        <div class="actions" style="justify-content:center; margin-top:28px;">
          <button class="btn btn-primary" type="button" data-modal-open>
            Start a Conversation <span class="arrow">â€º</span>
          </button>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/services">View Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
